#!/usr/bin/env python3
# shoexp - a (lovingly fake) Windows XP desktop drawn entirely with foot's
# vector-graphics protocol, driven by the mouse.
#
#   Run it:   ./bld/debug/foot sh -c 'python3 shoescripts/shoexp'
#   or, installed on PATH inside foot:   shoexp
#
# It's a joke demo: the iconic "Bliss" wallpaper, desktop icons, a Start menu
# and a blue taskbar with a live tray clock. Double-click an icon (or pick it
# from Start) to open a draggable window:
#
#   Calculator      a working clickable calculator
#   My Computer      drive icons + a capacity bar; double-click C: to browse
#   My Documents      a real file explorer rooted at your home folder
#   Recycle Bin      (it's empty, obviously)
#   Minesweeper      a real game (left reveal, right flag, smiley resets)
#   Notepad      a plain-text editor that captures the keyboard
#   Paint      drag to draw: pencil/line/rect/ellipse/eraser + palette
#   Internet Explorer  a (lovingly fake) IE6 with clickable canned pages
#
# The extra apps (Minesweeper, Notepad, Paint, Internet Explorer) each live in
# their own shoexp_<name>.py module and register through make_app(); the shared
# Canvas/palette helpers live in shoexp_ui.py.
#
# The file explorer ports slippers' Entry/Pane scan model, so it walks your
# ACTUAL filesystem - double-click folders to descend, ".." to go up.
#
# Like slippers, every frame is one comma-delimited DCS drawing program
# (ESC P > g ... ESC \) printed over itself at the home position. Mouse reports
# arrive as SGR-pixel coordinates that line up 1:1 with the canvas, so a click
# maps straight onto the drawn pixels - windows, buttons, icons and all.
#
# Mouse:  double-click desktop icons / drive rows / folders to open
#         drag a window by its title bar;  click controls _ and X
#         click Start for the menu;  click taskbar buttons to focus windows
#         wheel scrolls the file explorer
# Keys:   Esc closes the focused window (or the Start menu);  Ctrl-C quits;
#         q quits too unless a typing app (Notepad) has focus and eats it
#
# Env:  SHOEXP_FORCE=1     draw even if $TERM isn't foot-like
#       SHOEXP_PLAIN=1     never draw (print a notice and exit)
#       SHOEXP_SELFTEST=1  render one frame headless and exit (smoke check)
#
# Stdlib only; no dependencies.

